ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Course deals with theoretical formulation of various types of flow fields with varying conditions (viscous, inviscid, boundary layer in high Reynolds flows)I would not recommend for a biomedical engineer. May be more useful for mechanical engineer or applied physics.
A good course for students doing research in this area but not an introductary course.It depends.

Thorough description of theoretical fluid dynamics. I would not recommend to another student unless they are (1) familiar with Juan's teaching style and OK with it and (2) familiar with fluid dynamics already.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Help a little. More coverage of viscous flows would contribute more for my area.
It gave me an idea of the research in this area.
This course might contribute to my research in the future.
